{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"937f667e-609f-4da6-93d0-070bd15060f4","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_K9nk9nshwe1ZZeg9YXdLGL","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"225ca92e-7266-427c-8b81-3bb9328f699f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. **Environment variables** for .NET crash dump configuration\n2. **Kubernetes pod spec changes** (volume mounts, env vars, etc.)\n\nFor .NET crash dumps with NativeAOT, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables crash dumps\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` - optional diagnostics\n\nSince NativeAOT compiles the runtime directly into the app, I need to explicitly point to the `createdump` tool via `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`. I'll also need to set up a writable volume for storing the dump files and ensure proper permissions are configured.","outputTokens":427,"requestId":"C942:34C090:1E54EE0:2198F8F:6A052982"},"id":"9fe79210-450f-4e6c-af0c-839aba5575cc","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:46:53.044Z","parentId":"03fab194-47fd-44c3-975b-087ffe93e52f"}
