{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34b33b6a-6e1c-4a24-bdfe-cdf14c745ed0","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT on .NET 11:\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enables crash dumps |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full dump (use `2` for heap-only, `1` for mini) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/dumps/core.%p.%t` | Dump path with PID/timestamp tokens |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | **Required for NativeAOT** — the runtime doesn't bundle createdump |\n\n### Pod Spec Changes\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/core.%p.%t\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE          # createdump needs ptrace access\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi           # adjust based on app memory footprint\n```\n\n### Key notes\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** is critical for NativeAOT since the tool isn't embedded in the published output.\n- Use **`emptyDir`** for ephemeral collection, or swap to a **PersistentVolumeClaim** if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- Set `sizeLimit` to ~2× your app's working set to hold at least one full dump.\n- Dump type `4` (Full) is best for post-mortem debugging; use `2` (Heap) if size is a concern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"225ca92e-7266-427c-8b81-3bb9328f699f","outputTokens":591,"requestId":"C942:34C090:1E5757C:219BB20:6A05298C"},"id":"8a01f49a-c551-4892-be09-e8202a8c6a2d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:47:04.264Z","parentId":"0c274b03-09ed-4d58-9911-56083e32183d"}
